#: cards:1
msgid "Name Details"
msgstr "Ngā Taipitopito Imgoa"

#: cards:1
msgid ""
"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>The following guidelines are based on the National Council of Archives <em>Rules for the Construction of Personal, Place and Corporate Names.&nbsp;</em></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p><strong>Full Name</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>Use to record a concatenated form of the name. This can be useful for display or migration purposes but should not be used as a repalcement for the structured name data.</p>\n"
"\n"
"<p><strong>Title</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>In English only the titles Lord, Lady, Sir, Dame and Hon (Honourable) may precede the forename. However common practice allows for other titles, such as Mr, Mrs etc, to be used. Select the most appropriate.</p>\n"
"\n"
"<p><strong>Forename</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>A forename is the component of the name which a person is given in addition to his/her surname. All forenames, including middle names where known,&nbsp;should be listed to assist disambiguation between individuals.</p>\n"
"\n"
"<p><strong>Initials</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>These should only be used where the full name is not known&nbsp;or the individual is more usually known by their initials, eg. T.S. Eliot.&nbsp;</p>\n"
"\n"
"<p><strong>Surname</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>The component of a name which a person usually shares with other members of their family<strong>.</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p><strong>Epithet</strong></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>This is a word or phrase describing a person&#39;s status, position, occupation, nationality, place of birth etc. An epithet should be included as a qualifier where any confusion between persons may arise.</p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n"
"\n"
"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n"
msgstr ""
"<p>&nbsp;</p> \n"
"<p>&nbsp;</p> \n"
"<p>&nbsp;</p> \n"
"<p>Ko ngā tohutohu e whai ake nei i takea mai i te tuhinga a te National Council of Archives <em>Rules for the Construction of Personal, Place and Corporate Names.&nbsp;</em></p> \n"
"<p><strong>Ingoa Katoa</strong></p> \n"
"<p>Whakamahia hei tuhi i tētahi āhuatanga tūhono o te ingoa. Ka āhei te whakamahi i tēnei mō ngā take whakaatu, take whakawhiti rānei, engari kaua e whakamahia hei whakakapi mō ngā raraunga ingoa i āta whakaraupapatia.</p> \n"
"<p><strong>Taitara</strong></p> \n"
"<p>I te reo Pākehā heoi anō nei ngā taitara e āhei ana mō mua i te ingoa tuatahi ko ngā taitara Lord, Lady, Sir, Dame me Hon (Honourable). Ahakoa tērā, e whakaaetia ana ētahi atu ingoa nā te whānui o te whakamahi, pēnei i a Mr, i a Mrs, te aha, kia whakamahia. Tīpakona te mea tino hāngai.</p> \n"
"<p><strong>Ingoa tuatahi</strong></p> \n"
"<p>Ko te ingoa tuatahi te wae o te ingoa ka hoatu e te tangata i tua atu i tōna ingoa whānau. Me mātua whakarārangi ngā ingoa tuatahi katoa, tae atu ki ngā ingoa o waenganui: ina mōhiotia, kia kauparea atu te rangirua, kia mōhio pū ko wai a wai.</p> \n"
"<p><strong>Ngā Pū Tīmatanga</strong></p> \n"
"<p>Ka āhei te whakamahi e ēnei mō ngā ingoa anake kāore te ingoa katoa i te mōhiotia, e mōhiotia ana rānei te tangata mā ōna pū matua tuatahi, hei tauira, T.S. Eliot.&nbsp;</p> \n"
"<p><strong>Ingoa Whakamutunga</strong></p> \n"
"<p>Ko te wae o te ingoa o te tangata ka whakamahia tahitia e ia me ētahi atu mema o tōna whānau<strong>.</strong></p> \n"
"<p><strong>Kupuāhua</strong></p> \n"
"<p>He kupu, he kīanga tēnei e whakaahua ana i te tūnga o tētahi tangata, tōna tūranga, tāna mahi, tōna piringa ā-whenua, wāhi whānau, tōna aha. Me noho pea he kupuāhua i roto me ka rangirua te tangata ko wai rawa te tangata e kōrerotia ana./p> \n"
"<p>&nbsp;</p> \n"
"<p>&nbsp;</p>"

